# ðŸ§­ Curevia Website Setup & Deployment Guide

Minimal Hugo site built from scratch, styled without a theme.

---

## âœ… 1. Install Hugo

### macOS:

```bash
brew install hugo
```

### Linux:

```bash
sudo apt install hugo
```

### Windows (with Chocolatey):

```bash
choco install hugo -confirm
```

Check version:

```bash
hugo version
```

---

## âœ… 2. Set Up the Site

```bash
hugo new site curevia
cd curevia
```

Add folders:

```bash
mkdir -p layouts static/css static/images
```

Place files:

* `layouts/index.html` â†’ Your custom HTML
* `static/css/style.css` â†’ Styling
* `static/images/logo.png` â†’ Logo
* `static/images/hero-bg.jpg` â†’ Optional hero image

> ðŸ’¡ No theme is needed â€” layout is fully custom.

---

## âœ… 3. Add a Sample Post

```bash
hugo new posts/welcome.md
```

Edit `content/posts/welcome.md`:

```markdown
---
title: "Welcome to Curevia"
date: 2025-06-30
---

We're building the future of valve therapies.
```

---

## âœ… 4. Preview Locally

```bash
hugo server
```

Visit: [http://localhost:1313](http://localhost:1313)

---

## âœ… 5. Build the Site

```bash
hugo
```

Output goes to `public/` â€” ready for deployment.

---

## âœ… 6. GitHub Setup

### Initialize Git:

```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git branch -M main
```

### Connect Remote:

```bash
git remote add origin git@github.com:your-username/curevia-site.git
git push -u origin main
```

---

## âœ… 7. GitHub Actions Deployment

Create `.github/workflows/gh-pages.yml`:

```yaml
name: Deploy Hugo site to GitHub Pages

on:
  push:
    branches: [main]

jobs:
  deploy:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - uses: peaceiris/actions-hugo@v2
        with:
          hugo-version: 'latest'

      - run: hugo --minify

      - uses: peaceiris/actions-gh-pages@v3
        with:
          github_token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
          publish_dir: ./public
```

---

## âœ… 8. Enable GitHub Pages

1. Go to **Repo â†’ Settings â†’ Pages**
2. Set:

   * Branch: `gh-pages`
   * Folder: `/ (root)`

GitHub will give you a link like:

```
https://your-username.github.io/curevia-site/
```

---

## âœ… 9. Workflow Summary

| Task             | Command                                        |
| ---------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| Serve locally    | `hugo server`                                  |
| Build for deploy | `hugo`                                         |
| Push changes     | `git add . && git commit -m "..." && git push` |

